narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A performance class in which you perform about every other week before the class, get workshopped for about 20 minutes, then watch the others perform.
Absolutely! It's a pleasure of a class whether you love performing, love to watch people perform, want to get better, or all of the above!

Prepare one song every other week or so, write a couple of make-work papers, and have fun with musical theater once a week. Though it was sometimes frustrating to have a Friday afternoon class, I felt it was entirely worth it. Annette was really helpful in growing as a performer. This is not a vocal performance class, though, so if you're looking for that, find a private teacher.
